REASONING: Authoritative reference (Wikipedia) states: "The United States is divided into 50 states, plus the District of Columbia." — https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_states_and_territories_of_the_United_States
U.S. government source (USGS) defines the United States as: "The 50 States and the District of Columbia." — https://www.usgs.gov/faqs/what-constitutes-united-states-what-are-official-definitions
Encyclopedic reference (Britannica) describes the U.S. as "a federal republic of 50 states." — https://www.britannica.com/place/United-States
Therefore the claim "There are 51 states in America" is incorrect; the correct number of U.S. states is 50 (with the District of Columbia and various territories that are not states).
